---
/*
 * Shared `tjb run` terminal for the Bench surfaces (home Bench section and the
 * /bench page). Uses the site's .tline / .t-* terminal classes, so the output
 * is syntax-colored like the analyzer terminals AND wraps instead of chopping
 * the long command line (.tline is white-space: pre-wrap).
 */
---
<div class="terminal bench-terminal">
  <div class="terminal-titlebar">
    <span class="dot dot-r"></span><span class="dot dot-y"></span><span class="dot dot-g"></span>
    <span class="terminal-title">tjb</span>
  </div>
  <pre class="terminal-body bench-terminal-body"><span class="tline"><span class="t-prompt">$ </span><span class="t-cmd">tjb run --suite humaneval,gsm8k --baseline opus --candidate haiku</span></span>
<span class="tline t-dim">  running 200 paired tasks per suite…</span>
<span class="tline t-dim">  humaneval · 200/200   gsm8k · 200/200</span>
<span class="tline">  <span class="t-warn">humaneval REGRESSED</span>   <span class="t-success">gsm8k HOLDS</span></span>
<span class="tline t-label">  verdict → ./bench-report.json</span></pre>
</div>

<style>
  .bench-terminal { width: 100%; }
  .bench-terminal-body { padding: 14px 16px; margin: 0; font-size: 12.5px; line-height: 1.7; }
</style>
